CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F438A1784182683
OL,3,CWelsh Government lose Supplementary
OL,4,CBudget vote
OL,6,F"We remain committed to delivering
OL,7,Fthese priorities and we will continue
OL,8,Fto engage constructively with other
OL,9,FSenedd parties as we develop our
OL,10,Fspending plans in the Autumn."
OL,12,FOver the last few weeks, there have
OL,13,Fbeen no talks with Reform UK and the
OL,14,FConservatives. Instead negotiations
OL,15,Fwere held between Welsh Government
OL,16,Fministers and the Labour group which
OL,17,Ffocussed its demand on increased
OL,18,Ffunding for Additional Learning Needs
OL,19,F(ALN) in schools.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@^O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/11
